</m:mrow>
<m:mrow>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:mrow>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
<m:mi> ω </m:mi>
</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-87">
On the other hand, the linear acceleration of the belt is :
</para>
<para id="element-88">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mi> a </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:msub>
<m:mi> α </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mo> x </m:mo> 
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> r </m:mi>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
</m:msub>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mo> x </m:mo> 
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mn> 2 </m:mn>
<m:mo> = </m:mo> 
<m:mn> 4 </m:mn>
<m:mspace width="2pt"/>
<m:mi> m </m:mi>
